\pard\keep\keepn\widctlpar\s1\sb240\sa200\sl252\slmult1\cf2\f2\fs32 Installation\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\cf0\f1\fs22 There's no setup program. Extract files to a folder of your choice. Text (and RTF) files should be in a \i doc\i0  subdirectory and plugins (dll and other files) in a \i plugins32\i0  (32bit builds) or \i plugins64\i0  (64bit builds) subdirectory, although both types can also be in Steem's directory. \par
When you run a Steem SSE build for the first time, based on the file name, it proposes to add a link to the new version in your start menu if you care about that.\par
On starting, Steem SSE looks first in Documents/steem then in the application folder for your current steem.ini file, lastly in the registry. If it can't find it, it asks you where it is or it should be created (Steem creates a /steem directory that will contain steem.ini on that location). All your setting will be recorded in that file.\par
You must also select a TOS file (see Getting emulation started). One is provided (default tos.img).\par
\par

