\pard\keep\keepn\widctlpar\s1\sb240\sa200\sl252\slmult1\cf2\f2\fs32 Emulation limitations\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\cf0\f1\fs22 Emulation is mostly high-level with some low-level elements where it helps most. Define low-level! Steem SSE has a "low-level" 6301 emulation, in that the chip's opcodes are emulated instead of the high level commands sent to the chip, but the emulation of that chip is higher level than Steem's 68000 emulation, which is "high-level." Contrary to what you might think, really low-level emulation of all chips composing the ST is not realistic on current PC systems, as of 2021.\par
Emulation of the Mega ST and of the Mega STE is partial.\par
The light gun is not emulated (hard to do on a LCD screen!)\par
STE digital sound filters are not emulated (should we?). MicroWire isn't accurate.\par
Only one mouse in port 0 is emulated.\par
The MC68901 MFP's \i Pulse Width Measurement Operation\i0  isn't emulated. Timer B emulation is pragmatic and a bit dodgy.\par
SCP: Can't write disk images (they're all read-only anyway). Protections with weak bits can be trouble.\par
GEMDOS hard drive emulation is not guaranteed to be compatible with all programs (it's a hack after all).\par
Disk DMA transfer timing is approximate.\par
...\par
\par

\pard\keep\keepn\widctlpar\sb240\sa200\sl252\slmult1\cf2\f2\fs32\lang1033 Window menu\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\cf0\f1\fs22\lang2057 Press Alt-space for the Window menu, or click top left of the window, on the icon.\par
\i Restore Position\i0  is useful if some window was opened on another display which isn't currently switched on or similar circumstances. If Steem's main window is invisible, you can access the menu through the task bar.\par
When automatic resizing is off you may find it difficult to get the window to a precise size, making ugly lines appear.\par
Normal size will resize the window to the double (low res) size. Restore aspect ratio will maintain the current size of the window but will alter it so that its aspect ratio matches that of the selected size for the ST resolution. Also on this menu is Bigger and Smaller Window, they are a quick way to resize the window without going to the Options dialog, and border settings, which also affects the size of the window.\par
The window menu also lets you enable the tool bar and the classic menu, and start or stop emulation.\par
\par

\pard\keep\keepn\widctlpar\sb240\sa200\sl252\slmult1\cf2\f2\fs32\lang1033 Menu and Keyboard\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\cf0\f1\fs22\lang2057 If you press the Alt key while emulation is stopped, this toggles the classic menu. Most options of Steem SSE can be changed with just the keyboard.\par
\par

\pard\keep\keepn\widctlpar\sb240\sa200\sl252\slmult1\cf2\f2\fs32\lang1033 Getting emulation started\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\cf0\f1\fs22\lang2057 To use Steem, you need a copy of an Atari ROM with the operating system, called "TOS", and image disk files. A TOS file is 192KB long for the STF (except v2.06), 256KB for the STE. The extension is img or rom. When you first launch Steem SSE (no ini file), you must point to a TOS file, and you can change that later. One important point is to match ST model and TOS (see further), for example STF + TOS 1.02, STE + TOS 1.62.\par
In Steem v4.2 (and some older versions), TOS v2.06 (from Atari or from EmuTOS) works with the STF too. The UK version is included in the main download. The file is 256KB long (which is what Steem checks).\par
Use the disk manager or a shortcut to select the disk image, there are various ways to start emulation.\par
\par
Disk images are files that contain the data of a floppy disk. They are easy to find. For example:\par
{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK http://planetemu.net/index.php?section=menus&machine=34 }}{\fldrslt{http://planetemu.net/index.php?section=menus&machine=34\ul0\cf0}}}}\f1\fs22  \par
{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK http://www.atarimania.com/ }}{\fldrslt{http://www.atarimania.com/\ul0\cf0}}}}\f1\fs22\par
Unfortunately, full archives of ST programs are less available than they used to be.\par
\par
TOS:\par
{{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK http://www.avtandil.narod.ru/tose.html }}{\fldrslt{http://www.avtandil.narod.ru/tose.html\ul0\cf0}}}}\f1\fs22  \par
\par
Legally this is still copyrighted material, and if they really wanted, companies that own it could call a halt on emulation, but they don't. \par
\par
To get you started, a legal EmuTOS image is included in the download as the default tos.img.\par
\cf4 Tip\cf0  It crashes on accessories (ACC) and doesn't load DESKTOP.INF. Other than that, its compatibility is great. Both GEMDOS and ACSI hard drive emulations work with it. It works on both the STF (because we simulate hardware hacks!) and the STE.\par
\par

