\b RunOnStartup\par
\b0 This option is also in the GUI, and it also works when you double click on a configuration file in the Options dialog.\par
It should be placed in the [Options] part of your configuration file.\par
RunOnStartup=1\par
\par
\b Spurious\par
\b0 A spurious interrupt occurs when the MC68000 microprocessor is interrupted but the interrupt request (IRQ) clears during the \i interrupt acknowledge\i0  (IACK) cycle. On the ST, this may happen with the MFP. Emulation of this is tricky, you can deactivate it by changing this line in the [Options] part of your configuration file:\par
Spurious=0\par
\cf4 Tip\cf0  In Windows builds, this can be changed in the settings/emu parameters\par
\par
\b UsersPath and TempPath\par
\b0 At startup, Steem tries to determine where the main settings path and the temp path are. You can customize those in the ini file.\par
UsersPath=[path]\par
TempPath=[path]\par
The ini file may also contain the path of folders such as memory snapshots, shortcuts, etc.\par
\par

\pard\keep\keepn\widctlpar\sb240\sl252\slmult1\cf2\f2\fs32\lang1033 Debugging info\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa160\sl252\slmult1\cf0\f1\fs22\lang2057 If you check the TRACE.txt startup option, Steem SSE saves a log with that name containing some useful information in its running directory each time it is stopped. \par
\par
It is possible to read the trace file from inside Steem SSE, in the info dialog. Notice that Windows will need time to update the dialog if the file is large (but it eventually does).\par
\par
Sometimes, a fatal error happens (system exception). Windows builds of Steem SSE tries to catch them instead of just crashing. To help reporting, an alert box describes the error. The message is also copied into the Trace file. If the bug happens in Steem SSE itself, it's sometimes possible to track it down using this message.\par
\par
If you post a bug report, please read the rules before (on the website forum). Ask yourself if you're giving all useful information to get the bug fixed or if you're just venting frustration like a lamer.\par
Don't forget to copy or join the TRACE.txt (report on the last run) and options.txt (complete dump of your options when leaving Steem) files if appropriate. To protect your privacy, file paths are redacted (except for GEMDOS hard drive emulation).\par
